{
  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n\r\n    \r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">SIGNIFICANT FIGURES AND DECIMAL PLACES&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Notice the difference between significant figures and decimal places. In Significant figures we start counting from a whole number that is not zero, while in decimal places, we start counting from the decimal point.<\/span><\/p>\r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">What is the difference between 1.867551 correct to four significant figures and 1.867551 correct four decimal places?<\/span><\/p>\r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. 5 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-1<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">, B. 4 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-4<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">, C. 5 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-4<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">, D. 10 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-3<\/sup><\/span><\/p>\r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B(2005\/2006 no 2).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1.867551 correct to four significant figures = 1.868<\/span><\/p>\r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1.867551 correct four decimal places = 1.8676<\/span><\/p>\r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Difference means subtraction<\/span><\/p>\r\n    <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1.868 - 1.8676 = 0.0004 = 4 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-4<\/sup><\/span><\/p>\r\n\r\n \r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "SIGNIFICANT FIGURES AND DECIMAL PLACES"
}